         <region style="defaultSpeaker" xml:id="speaker"></region>
      </layout>
   </head>
   <body xml:id="thebody" style="defaultCaption">
      <div xml:lang="en">
         <p begin="00:00:07.96" end="00:00:10.16" region="speaker">At some point, you may wish to export your</p>
         <p begin="00:00:10.16" end="00:00:13.23" region="speaker">digital certificate, for example, To back up your</p>
         <p begin="00:00:13.23" end="00:00:15.50" region="speaker">digital certificate, Install your digital</p>
         <p begin="00:00:15.50" end="00:00:18.20" region="speaker">certificate on a different or new computer, For</p>
         <p begin="00:00:18.20" end="00:00:21.70" region="speaker">temporary use, or For using different browsers</p>
         <p begin="00:00:21.70" end="00:00:24.00" region="speaker">You can export your digital certificate if it</p>
         <p begin="00:00:24.00" end="00:00:25.86" region="speaker">has been marked as exportable during its</p>
         <p begin="00:00:25.86" end="00:00:27.23" region="speaker">installation.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:27.23" end="00:00:30.33" region="speaker">In your browser&apos;s &quot;Menu bar&quot; click &quot;Tools&quot; and</p>
         <p begin="00:00:30.33" end="00:00:32.30" region="speaker">then &quot;Options.&quot;</p>
         <p begin="00:00:32.30" end="00:00:35.50" region="speaker">Open the &quot;Advanced&quot; tab.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:35.50" end="00:00:38.23" region="speaker">Then click the &quot;Encryption&quot; tab.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:38.23" end="00:00:40.86" region="speaker">Click the &quot;View Certificates&quot; button.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:40.86" end="00:00:42.70" region="speaker">Make sure the &quot;Your Certificates&quot; tab is</p>
         <p begin="00:00:42.70" end="00:00:46.30" region="speaker">selected. Click the Digital Certificate that you would</p>
         <p begin="00:00:46.30" end="00:00:50.23" region="speaker">like to backup and then click the &quot;Backup&quot; button.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:50.23" end="00:00:53.00" region="speaker">Choose a location to export orbackup your</p>
         <p begin="00:00:53.00" end="00:00:55.00" region="speaker">certificate.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:56.36" end="00:00:60.46" region="speaker">Name the file, as appropriate, and then</p>
         <p begin="00:00:60.46" end="00:00:63.96" region="speaker">click the &quot;Save&quot; button Next, you must create a</p>
         <p begin="00:00:63.96" end="00:00:66.30" region="speaker">&quot;Backup Password&quot; to protect the certificate</p>
         <p begin="00:00:66.30" end="00:00:67.30" region="speaker">that you are creating.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:67.30" end="00:00:70.03" region="speaker">This step is mandatory in the backup process and</p>
         <p begin="00:00:70.03" end="00:00:70.66" region="speaker">must be completed to proceed.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:70.66" end="00:00:74.26" region="speaker">Note that you will not be able to access this backup</p>
         <p begin="00:00:74.26" end="00:00:76.96" region="speaker">certificate at a later time without the password.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:76.96" end="00:00:79.33" region="speaker">Make certain that you are able to remember it or</p>
         <p begin="00:00:79.33" end="00:00:82.33" region="speaker">that you write it down and keep it in a safe place.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:82.33" end="00:00:84.36" region="speaker">A built-in meter will display the quality of</p>
         <p begin="00:00:84.36" end="00:00:86.40" region="speaker">your password&apos;s strength.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:86.40" end="00:00:87.40" region="speaker">Click OK.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:87.40" end="00:00:90.63" region="speaker">A message will appear informing you of the</p>
         <p begin="00:00:90.63" end="00:00:92.70" region="speaker">successful digital certificate backup</p>
         <p begin="00:00:92.70" end="00:00:94.33" region="speaker">creation.</p>
         <p begin="00:00:94.33" end="00:00:97.50" region="speaker">Click OK You may now move your certificate as</p>
         <p begin="00:00:97.50" end="00:00:98.83" region="speaker">needed.</p>
    </div>
